<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-26T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163AM33/95: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-26T20:00:00+09:00">August 26, 1938—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 26—9:16 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>560. Department’s 297, August 25, 4 p.m.,<note n="73" xml:id="d614fn73">Not printed.</note> bombing of Southern Baptist Mission at Pingtu.
                            In conference today with the Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs I drew
                            his attention to our note No. 975 of June 28,<note n="74" xml:id="d614fn74"><ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_604"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 604</ref>.</note> which has
                            not been answered and asked for an early reply. Horinouchi promised
                            immediate investigation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>